                <note rend="inline" type="source">813.00 Tacoma/–: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ramer</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="49" xml:id="d155fn49">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                            mutandis</hi>, to the Ministers in Honduras (no. 31) and Salvador (no.
                        42).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-25T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 25, 1922—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>33. You will transmit to President Chamorro the following message from the
                    President: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“It is with great satisfaction and gratification that I learn that Your
                            Excellency was enabled by the meeting on board the U. S. S. <hi
                                rend="italic">Tacoma</hi> to arrive at an agreement with the
                            Presidents of El Salvador and Honduras with a view to maintaining
                            amicable fraternal relations of good will and peace among your
                            countries. It was a great pleasure to be able to assist this conference
                            in any way, and I <pb facs="0546" n="426" xml:id="pg_426"/> assure you
                            of the continued interest of the United States Government and people, as
                            well as my own personal interest in the welfare of your country. Warren
                            G. Harding.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
